<p>Forty minutes later you straighten up and stand with your hands on your knees, catching your breath. Every muscle in your body has been reminded it exists.</p>
<p>It's {{ time_str "HH:mm" }}. You're sweaty and your legs are shaky in the best possible way.</p>
[[Shower (Bathroom), home_bathroom]]
[[Stay in the living room, home_livingroom]]
#end

#begin yoga
You find a clear patch of floor, fold a blanket into a rough mat, and take off your shoes.
<p>You start with child's pose — forehead to the ground, arms stretched forward, breathing long and slow until your spine unclenches. From there you move through what you remember: cat-cow, downward dog, a warrior sequence that your hips protest mildly before they give in.</p>
<p>There's no instructor, no mirror, no pressure. Just the sound of traffic outside and your own slow breathing.</p>
{{ roll_yoga = random_int 1 5 }}
{{ if roll_yoga == 1 }}
<p>At some point — somewhere in a long hip-opener stretch, one leg folded beneath you — you stop thinking and just feel. The warmth in your muscles. The give of your body. Something slow and pleasant hums at the edges of your awareness.</p>
{{ attr_change "mc" "horny" 8 }}
{{ end }}
{{ advance_time 25 }}
{{ attr_change "mc" "energy" -8 }}
{{ attr_change "mc" "agility" 3 }}
{{ attr_change "mc" "mood" 12 }}
<p>When you finally sit cross-legged and close your eyes for the last two minutes, the room feels quieter than it did before. It's {{ time_str "HH:mm" }}.</p>
<p>You feel like you've done something kind for yourself.</p>
[[Living Room, home_livingroom]]
#end
